practice to run a selfservice laundry and drycleaning business 
because the wash carries a lot less liability than medicine 
when doctors have a malpractice suit its a 3 million to 5 
million loss if someones laundry doesnt come out right i just 
pay them the 40 or so to cover it and its done said dr joseph 
j merigo 
merigo 57 took over the hudson coinop on march 1 he said 
insurance rates drove him out of his 20year practice as an 
anesthesiologist at bostonarea hospitals 
a lot of people think you make a lot of money as a doctor 
merigo said but you dont have any choice your bills are so 
high 
merigo said his liability insurance premiums just about equal 
his annual income although he has never been sued 
merigo still works three mornings a week at bournewood hospital 
a psychiatric facility in brookline whose electroconvulsive 
therapy center he helped found he will stop practicing medicine 
oct 23 when his insurance policy runs out 
he admitted to some hesitation about the career switch you 
dont get the same kick from doing a suit that you do after doing a 
