five more bodies were found friday in a 
mound of debris in the sikhs bulletscarred golden temple in 
punjab state the press trust of india reported 
that increased the number of bodies of hostages recovered from 
the temple complex to 21 the news agency said 
militant sikhs who surrendered after troops assaulted the temple 
in amritsar last month said the sikh separatists had held at least 
40 people as hostages in the complex before the army siege began 
based on that report soldiers are still searching for the bodies of 
19 other victims 
united news of india said the militants extorted money from the 
captives families on the false promise that they would be freed 
it said among the victims were four women and it was believed 
the hostages had been tortured before they were killed in the 
temple complex in amritsar 260 miles northwest of new delhi the 
temple is the sikhs holiest shrine 
more than 200 sikh militants surrendered after the 10day siege 
of the temple ended on may 18 during the siege 41 sikh fighters 
were killed along with five civilians caught in the crossfire 
according to authorities 
they said the hostages were killed by the militants before and 
during the siege 
sikh activists have been blamed for killing more than 1240 
people in northern punjab state this year in their batle for an 
independent homeland 
sikhs form 2 percent of indias population of 800 million people 
but are in a majority in punjab the separatists launched their war 
in 1982 claiming discrimination by hindus who comprise 80 percent 
of the population 
