money farmers actually get out of it most likely will rise 66 
percent this year to a total of 302 billion according to the 
analysis 
spending for domestically produced food is expected to rise 4eside 
livestock and poultry supplies are 
causing the change a 50cent cut in the milk support price is 
expected to result in somewhat lower return to the dairy farmer 
despite a slight increase in consumption 
