noone was reported injured by the quake which registered 65 
on the richter scale police said 
in washington the us geological survey reported that the 
quake was the strongest tremor in the general area in more than 12 
years since a magnitude 67 earthquake on may 4 1976 
the 1137 am quake was centered in the southern alps near the 
southwest corner of south island near lake te anau and about 450 
miles southwest of wellington 
