<TEXT>
here is a chronology of the dramatic 
rescue of the six miners at the stolzenbach mine as provided by 
heinz cramer a member of the board of mine owner preussen elektra 
late friday rescuers drill a ventilation hole over the eastern 
section of the mine to pump fresh air into the shaft 
at about 910 pm friday rescuers detect tapping sounds 
through the hole they first try to verify the sounds with a 
stethoscope 
shortly after midnight a directional microphone provided by a 
television crew is lowered into the hole rescuers hear the 
following faint words they have drilled a hole 
at 230 am rescuers hear distinct regular tapping sounds 
at 4 am the first rescue team descends into the shaft to look 
for the survivors carrying medicine and bandages a second crew 
follows shortly afterward 
at 421 am rescuers detect human figures in the dark 
approach the area and find the six survivors the survivors are 
given oxygen breathing devices and are able to walk on their own 
about 15 miles to a main ventilation shaft used by rescuers to 
enter the mine 
at 525 am rescuers and survivors reach the ventilation 
shaft a special rescue cage is lowered into the shaft 
at 530 am heinz roese is the first survivor to be pulled to 
the surface the other five are pulled up within 45 minutes 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

