<TEXT>
yearly summit meetings between us and japanese 
leaders would strengthen ties and help establish global stability 
and economic progress says a report by researchers and politicians 
from both countries 
the study released friday by the japaneseamerican study 
committee on comprehensive security also calls for the creation of 
a permanent nongovernmental council to advise leaders on issues 
that affect both nations 
cochairmen of the committee were former us undersecretary of 
state philip c habib and former japanese ambassador to the united 
states yoshio okawara it is sponsored by the honolulubased 
organization pacific forum and the asia pacific association of japan 
the united states and japan collectively represent the most 
significant force for global stability and economic progress the 
report says together the two countries can make unparalleled 
contributions to global peace stability and economic development 
the report titled creative engagement stategies for united 
statesjapan global cooperation toward the 21st century calls for 
greater cooperation between the two countries on common strategic 
and economic objectives 
in order to live and work together successfully the united 
states and japan must develop a shared vision of their future and a 
set of institutional arrangements that broaden and deepen the 
complex bilateral interdependence that already binds them the 
report says 
the committee said summit meetings held each year between the 
us president and japanese prime minister would help focus 
attention on a mutually beneficial relationship and establish 
deadlines for policies that spur cooperation between the countries 
it will be especially important to hold a summit early in the 
new us administration and preparations should begin in both tokyo 
and washington immediately after the november us election the 
report said 
the committee said the relationship also would be helped by the 
creation of an americajapan council to examine issues and advise 
government leaders 
the council would be publicly and privately funded and its 
members would represent private and public sectors affected by 
issues of mutual interest between the united states and japan the 
report said 
the report also called on japan to increase its military capacity 
to perform missions within the framework of a usjapanese alliance 
the pacific forum is an independent institution with a goal of 
fostering regional security and prosperity among the nations of the 
asiapacific region habib is chairman of the pacific forums board 
of directors 
</TEXT>
