rescuers found the bodies of 
four miners saturday bringing the death toll from a rockburst in 
the worlds deepest gold mine to seven 
the bursting of the rock which is caused by underground 
earthquakes or tremendous pressures at great depths occurred friday 
night 6600 feet beneath the surface at western deep levels gold 
mine 
three bodies were recovered immediately and rescue operations 
continued until the rest were found saturday evening 
a spokesman for the mine owner anglo american corp said the 
victims next of kin had not yet been notified 
the rockburst occurred in the western shaft one of two shafts 
at western deep levels that extend more than 13000 feet underground 
the mine 43 miles west of johannesburg is unique in that it 
operates at such deep levels and is in a geologically unstable area 
said anglo spokesman james duncan 
the mining company has pioneered methods of predicting and 
minimizing the danger from rockbursts but they are a fact of 
life there said duncan 
